# Resident Evil - Bullet Hell Game

## Project Summary

Single-player bullet hell game on real-world Mapbox map. Player moves (WASD), shoots toward mouse, zombies spawn around. Position saved periodically (5 min or shortcut).

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Frontend | React, Mapbox GL, PixiJS/Phaser (game render) |
| Backend | NestJS |
| Database | PostgreSQL (Supabase) |
| Cache | Redis |
| Map | Mapbox (zoom 18-20 for street level) |
| Deploy | Vercel (frontend), Railway/Render (backend) |

## Architecture

- **Monorepo**: `backend/` (NestJS), `frontend/` (React)
- **Docker**: `docker-compose.yml` for local dev
- **Single player first** - no real-time sync initially

## Key Conventions

- **Docker-first**: Luôn dùng Docker/container cho Node, npm, dev - không chạy trên host (xem `docker-workflow.mdc`)
- Vietnamese or English in comments/docs - be consistent per file
- Keep MCP integration experimental, minimal scope
